e other paladins of Charlemagne, and in recent times by the ceramic artist  Clarice Cliff  (  1899–1972 )."],"variants":[{"name":"Claris","meanings":["Medieval English and French form of the Latin name <i>Claritia</i>. This may have meant ‘fame’ (an abstract derivative of <i>clārus</i> ‘famous’), but as a given name it may have been no more than an arbitrary elaboration of   Clara .  It was borne by a character who features in some versions of the medieval romances of Roland and the other paladins of Charlemagne, and in recent times by the ceramic artist  Clarice Cliff  (  1899–1972 )."]},{"name":"Clarisse","meanings":["Medieval English and French form of the Latin name <i>Claritia</i>. This may have meant ‘fame’ (an abstract derivative of <i>clārus</i> ‘famous’), but as a given name it may have been no more than an arbitrary elaboration of   Clara .  It was borne by a character who features in some versions of the medieval romances of Roland and the other paladins of Charlemagne, and in recent times by the ceramic artist  Clarice Cliff  (  1899–1972 )."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705190,"age":5,"year":"1290","julianDay":2192224,"title":"Jews Expelled From England","description":"After years of anti-Semitic behavior, King Edward I expelled Jews from England in 1290.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705191,"age":30,"year":"1315","toYear":"1317","julianDay":2201354,"title":"Famine Strikes Europe","description":"A famine caused by cold winters and wet summers across Europe caused millions to die due to starvation. Desperation from hunger caused high levels of crime, stampedes in bread lines in London, infanticide, and even cannibalism throughout Europe.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705192,"age":43,"year":"1328","julianDay":2206102,"title":"First War of Scottish Independence","description":"The First War of Scottish Independence began after England invaded Scotland in 1296. The Treaty of Edinburgh was signed in 1328 which declared peace between the two kingdoms and b